  "title": "Immigration Consultant (Sales)",
  "description": "<p>Job Responsibilities:</p><p>1. Communicate professionally with high-net-worth clients to understand their immigration needs and develop tailored proposals.</p><p>2. Proactively engage potential clients through outreach, appointment scheduling, and relationship-building.</p><p>3. Manage client follow-ups, address concerns, and facilitate timely deal closures.</p><p>4. Uphold the company’s reputation by ensuring a high standard of service and client satisfaction.</p><p>5. Stay informed on global immigration programs and regulations to provide accurate, up-to-date advice.</p><p><br />Requirements:</p><p>1. Minimum Diploma or Degree qualification</p><p>2. At least 1-2 year of sales experience, preferably in a client-facing role</p><p>3. Strong ability to multitask and excel in a fast-paced, collaborative environment</p><p>4. Quick thinking and resourcefulness to adapt to dynamic situations</p><p>5. Excellent interpersonal skills with the ability to manage cross-functional stakeholders</p><p>6. Strong planning and organizational skills to effectively manage time and resources</p><p><br />Benefits:</p><p>1. Convenient office location near Raffles Place MRT stations</p><p>2. Working hours: Monday to Friday: 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM, Saturday (only once in a month): 9.00AM - 6.00 PM</p><p>3. Supportive yet challenging work environment, engaging with high-net-worth clients</p><p>4. Excellent opportunities for internal career progression and cross-border transfers</p>",
